Filters:
    - filters are used to format the data accroding to application requirement.

    - we have two types of filters.

        1. predefined filters

        2. custom filters.

predefined filters:
    - the filters given by the framework called as predefined filters.

custom filters:
    - the filters developed by developer based on application requirement called as custom filter.

1.uppercase
    - used to convert the lowercase characters to uppercase.

2. lowercase
    - used to convert the uppercase characters to lowercase.

3. currency
    - used to append the "$" symbol to the numerical values.

4. orderBy
    - used to sort the data either "assending order" or "decending order"

5. limitTo
    - this filter used to display the required number of records from an array.

6. filter
    - this filter used to search the whole array based on user input.

7.date
    - this filter used to format the date accroding to application requirement.

custom filters:
--------------
<h1>{{"hello" | reverse }}
app.filter("reverse",reverse);
function reverse(){
    //syntax of custom filters
    return function(arg1){
        var data="";  //h
        for(var i=0;i<arg1.length;i++){
            data = arg1[i]+data;
        }
        return data;
    }
}

Ex_2:
<h1>{{100 | my_currency : "₹" : true}}</h1>   //₹ 100
<h1>{{200 | my_currency : "£" : false}}</h1> // 200 £

app.filter("my_currency",my_currency);
function my_currency(){
    return function(amount,symbol,position){
        if(position){
            return symbol+amount;
        }else{
            return amount+symbol;
        }
    }
}
























